.TH "simple_shell" "1" "12 april 2021" "version 1.0" "hsh man page"
.hy
.SH PROLOG
.PP
This manual page is part of a collaborative project, where the operation of a
shell is evaluated in order to replicate it.
.PP
.SH NAME
.PP
hsh \[en] command language interpreter.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]\f[R]
.PP
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
The simple_shell or ./hsh is a program that interprets the commands given by the
 user.
.PP
.SH EXAMPLE
.PP
To run the program you have to compile all the .c files contained in the
repository with the following command:
.PP
.ft BI
$ gcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic *.c -o hsh
.PP
In interactive mode:
.PP
.ft BI
$ ./hsh
.PP
.ft BI
$ pwd
.PP
.ft BI
/home/simple_shell/
.PP
.ft BI
$ exit
.PP
In non-interactive mode:
.PP
.ft BI
$ echo "pwd" | ./hsh
.PP
.ft BI
/home/simple_shell/
.PP
.SH COMMANDS
.PP
Some commands that can be run with hsh:
.PP
.ft BI
PATH commands.
.PP
Locate the required command (ls, pwd, ...) in the PATH file and run it.
.PP
.ft BI
env
.PP
Prints the current environment.
.PP
.ft BI
exit
.PP
End all process.
.PP
.SH BUGS
.PP
They are not known yet.
.PP
.SH AUTHOR
.PP
Aguie Clavijo, Julieth Gonzalez and Carlos Polania.